I"¶<p>Today, the Office of Li Zhaozhi through its Press Office released the revised version of the Action Plan on web development. This updated Action Plan will overwrite and succeed the older version that shall be treated as the guidebook for learning web development knowledge and skills.</p>

<p>The document is divided into six chapters. The first chapter sets the objective of the Action Plan and offers a high-level glance of the document structure. The second chapter explains why is it meaningful and important to acquire web development skills to design web-based applications and build a full-stack web design system. The third chapter sets learning objectives in the technology, design, functionality and analytics components of web applications. The fourth chapter explains how the Plan will measure success. The fifth chapter details how the Action Plan will achieve these objectives through a combination of learning methods. Finally, the sixth chapter summarises the Plan and outlines implementation rules.</p>

<p>In addition to the above chapters, the document includes two appendix attachments that offer tools to track progress and measure the effectiveness of the Plan.</p>

<p>This document is made available in Simplified Chinese. You can download the PDF-converted Action Plan and the two attachments below.</p>

